  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "CUSTOMER SERVICE EXECUTIVES AND MANAGERS",
  "description": "<p>If you are meticulous, sales driven and love working with children, a career with Dancepointe may be just what you are looking for! You will be rewarded with competitive remuneration and benefits. And, throughout your career, enjoy opportunities and training designed for your professional and personal development.​<br /></p><p><strong>Only Full time Positions Available.</strong> You will perform the duty of daily administrations and operations of Dancepointe Academy. The roles and responsibilities are as follows:</p><ul><li>Customer service for parents and general inquiries</li><li>Administration of teachers and students</li><li>Invoicing of school fees</li><li>Coordination of class schedules</li><li>Preparation of term reports</li><li>Maintenance of inventory records</li><li>Organization of new enrolments and classes</li><li>Promotion and sale of dance courses and dance wear</li></ul><p>As an Operations Manager, you will oversee a cluster of branches and lead a team of executives to achieve the company's overall objectives.​</p><p><strong>Requirements For Customer Service Executives and Managers:</strong></p><ul><li>Min. O levels/ Diploma</li></ul><ul><li>With at least 3 years of administration or retail experiences preferred. For managers, we will require minimum 6 years experience.</li><li>Candidate with dance background will be added advantage</li><li>Possess strong communication and computer skills, self-motivated and sales driven</li><li>Able to work on Weekday nights and Weekends.</li><li>5 days work week </li></ul><p>Join our team and grow together with us today!</p>",
